\chapter{Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui}
\label{\detokenize{index:module-Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui}}\label{\detokenize{index:fralysis-gui-inputoutputgui}}\index{Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui (module)@\spxentry{Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui}\spxextra{module}}
Thread to parse data between view and controller
\index{daemon (in module Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui)@\spxentry{daemon}\spxextra{in module Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{index:Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui.daemon}}\pysigline{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui.}}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{daemon}}}
A boolean value indicating whether this thread is a daemon thread.

This must be set before start() is called, otherwise RuntimeError is
raised. Its initial value is inherited from the creating thread; the
main thread is not a daemon thread and therefore all threads created in
the main thread default to daemon = False.

The entire Python program exits when no alive non-daemon threads are
left.

\end{fulllineitems}

\index{ident (in module Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui)@\spxentry{ident}\spxextra{in module Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{index:Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui.ident}}\pysigline{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui.}}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{ident}}}
Thread identifier of this thread or None if it has not been started.

This is a nonzero integer. See the get\_ident() function. Thread
identifiers may be recycled when a thread exits and another thread is
created. The identifier is available even after the thread has exited.

\end{fulllineitems}

\index{name (in module Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui)@\spxentry{name}\spxextra{in module Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{index:Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui.name}}\pysigline{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{Fralysis.GUI.InputOutputGui.}}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{name}}}
A string used for identification purposes only.

It has no semantics. Multiple threads may be given the same name. The
initial name is set by the constructor.

\end{fulllineitems}

\index{user\_data\_dir (in module Fralysis.GUI.MainApp)@\spxentry{user\_data\_dir}\spxextra{in module Fralysis.GUI.MainApp}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{index:Fralysis.GUI.MainApp.user_data_dir}}\pysigline{\sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{Fralysis.GUI.MainApp.}}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{user\_data\_dir}}}~
\DUrole{versionmodified,added}{New in version 1.7.0.}

Returns the path to the directory in the users file system which the
application can use to store additional data.

Different platforms have different conventions with regards to where
the user can store data such as preferences, saved games and settings.
This function implements these conventions. The \textless{}app\_name\textgreater{} directory
is created when the property is called, unless it already exists.

On iOS, \sphinxtitleref{\textasciitilde{}/Documents/\textless{}app\_name\textgreater{}} is returned (which is inside the
app’s sandbox).

On Android, \sphinxtitleref{/sdcard/\textless{}app\_name\textgreater{}} is returned.

On Windows, \sphinxtitleref{\%APPDATA\%/\textless{}app\_name\textgreater{}} is returned.

On OS X, \sphinxtitleref{\textasciitilde{}/Library/Application Support/\textless{}app\_name\textgreater{}} is returned.

On Linux, \sphinxtitleref{\$XDG\_CONFIG\_HOME/\textless{}app\_name\textgreater{}} is returned.

\end{fulllineitems}
